top 5 의 status¶

In [69]:
abengers_total_top5=abengers_df.sort_values(by=['Total'], axis=0).tail(5)#,ascending=False
abengers_total_top5=abengers_total_top5.reset_index(drop=True)

labels = abengers_total_top5.columns[2:-1]
num_labels = len(labels)


angles = [x/float(num_labels)*(2*pi) for x in range(num_labels)] ##  
angles += angles[:1] ##     

my_palette = plt.cm.get_cmap("Set2", len(abengers_total_top5.index))
 
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,20))
fig.set_facecolor('white')

for i, row in abengers_total_top5.iterrows():
    color = my_palette(i)
    #data = abengers_total.iloc[i].drop(['Name','Alignment','Total']).tolist()
    data = abengers_total_top5.iloc[i].drop(['Name','Alignment','Total']).tolist()
    data += data[:1]

    
    ax = plt.subplot(3,2,i+1, polar=True)
    ax.set_theta_offset(pi / 2) ## 
    ax.set_theta_direction(-1) ##   
    
    plt.xticks(angles[:-1], labels, fontsize=13) ## x  
    ax.tick_params(axis='x', which='major', pad=15) ## x    .
 
    ax.set_rlabel_position(0) ## y  (degree )
    plt.yticks([0,20,40,60,80,100],['0','20','40','60','80','100'], fontsize=10) ## y  
    plt.ylim(0,100)
    
    ax.plot(angles, data, color=color, linewidth=2, linestyle='solid') ##   
    ax.fill(angles, data, color=color, alpha=0.4) ##    .

    
    plt.title(row.Name, size=20, color=color,x=-0.2, y=1, ha='left') ##    .

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns


%matplotlib inline 



salary_1819=pd.read_csv('./salary_201819.csv')
salary_18=pd.read_csv('./IT Salary Survey EU 2018.csv')
salary_19=pd.read_csv('./IT Salary Survey EU 2019.csv')
salary_20=pd.read_csv('./IT Salary Survey EU  2020.csv')


plt.figure(figsize=(20,5))
salary_18_by_level=salary_18.groupby(['Your level']).count()
ratio=salary_18_by_level['Current Salary']
labels = ['Head', 'Junior', 'Senior']
explode = [0.01, 0.01, 0.01]
colors = ['gold', 'whitesmoke', 'silver']
wedgeprops={'width': 0.7, 'edgecolor': 'w', 'linewidth': 5}
plt.subplot(131)
plt.pie(ratio, labels=labels, autopct='%.1f%%',explode=explode,colors=colors, wedgeprops=wedgeprops)
title='18` Seniority Level'
plt.title(title)



salary_19_by_level=salary_19.groupby(['Seniority level']).count()
ratio = salary_19_by_level['Zeitstempel']
labels = ['Head', 'Junior', 'Lead', 'Middle','Principal','Senior']
explode = [0.1,0.1,0.01,0.01,0.01,0.1]
colors = ['gold', 'whitesmoke', 'lightgray', 'lightgray','lightgray','silver']
#wedgeprops={'width': 0.7, 'edgecolor': 'w', 'linewidth': 5}
plt.subplot(132)
plt.pie(ratio, labels=labels, autopct='%.1f%%',explode=explode,colors=colors)#, wedgeprops=wedgeprops
title='19` Seniority Level'
plt.title(title)



salary_20_by_level=salary_20.groupby(['Seniority level']).count()
ratio=salary_20_by_level.sort_values(by=['Timestamp'],axis=0).tail(6)['Timestamp']
labels = ['Principal', 'Head', 'Junior', 'Lead','Middle','Senior']
explode = [0.01,0.1,0.1,0.01,0.01,0.1]
colors = ['lightgray', 'gold', 'whitesmoke', 'lightgray','lightgray','silver']
#wedgeprops={'width': 0.7, 'edgecolor': 'w', 'linewidth': 5}
plt.subplot(133)
plt.pie(ratio, labels=labels, autopct='%.1f%%',explode=explode,colors=colors)#, wedgeprops=wedgeprops
title='20` Seniority Level'
plt.title(title)
plt.show()
